I bet you loved her very much.

00:16:43.961 --> 00:16:46.547
It's okay.
It's okay.

00:16:46.630 --> 00:16:47.965
It's okay.

00:16:48.048 --> 00:16:49.550
No.

00:16:49.633 --> 00:16:53.887
It's okay, it's okay.

00:16:53.971 --> 00:16:56.223
It's okay.

00:16:56.306 --> 00:16:58.684
What's going on?

00:17:00.978 --> 00:17:02.855
It's okay.

00:17:02.938 --> 00:17:04.647
I'm gonna cry.

00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:07.401
So this was fun.

00:17:07.483 --> 00:17:10.863
Text us when you get a home.
So, so nice.

00:17:10.945 --> 00:17:13.824
We should make sure to do
this again, like, this year.

00:17:13.906 --> 00:17:15.534
Totally.
No.

00:17:15.617 --> 00:17:17.703
100%.
No, no, no, no, no!

00:17:17.786 --> 00:17:19.788
We only get this day once.

00:17:19.872 --> 00:17:21.749
I mean, we're not
getting it back.

00:17:21.832 --> 00:17:24.626
So let's do it.
I mean, let's really do it.

00:17:24.710 --> 00:17:26.252
Let's... let's do the day.

00:17:26.336 --> 00:17:28.338
Okay, what do you wanna do?

00:17:28.422 --> 00:17:29.757
I don't know.

00:17:29.840 --> 00:17:33.886
Let's see where
the tide sails us, huh?

00:17:33.969 --> 00:17:35.512
Fun.

00:17:50.694 --> 00:17:53.197
You got through it, you did.
Shit everywhere.

00:17:59.495 --> 00:18:02.122
Oh, my gosh.

00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:05.584
It's our old apartment.

00:18:05.667 --> 00:18:07.795
Wow.
It's a different era.

00:18:07.878 --> 00:18:10.130
Don't you guys wish
we could go in and, like,

00:18:10.214 --> 00:18:12.758
go back in time?

00:18:12.841 --> 00:18:15.385
Why don't we?
Well, I moved out, you know.

00:18:15.469 --> 00:18:17.638
I'm sorry, your kidnapper made
it seem like you wanted

00:18:17.721 --> 00:18:19.973
to move out
so I-I moved us out.

00:18:20.057 --> 00:18:21.975
Okay, but I think
we should try and see

00:18:22.059 --> 00:18:24.812
what it looks like inside.
Wouldn't that be fun?

00:18:24.895 --> 00:18:27.356
Really? What if
there are people in there?

00:18:27.439 --> 00:18:29.233
Then we ask them
to let us in.

00:18:29.316 --> 00:18:31.485
If nobody lives there,
then we just break in.

00:18:31.568 --> 00:18:33.445
Come on.
Live a little.

00:18:33.529 --> 00:18:36.240
Aah, I'm ticklish.
Don't tickle me.

00:18:36.323 --> 00:18:39.284
I'm scared to say
no to you so let's.

00:18:39.368 --> 00:18:41.954
This is so, so,
so, so stupid.

00:18:42.037 --> 00:18:44.164
Okay, how do you even know
how to pick locks?

00:18:44.248 --> 00:18:45.791
I can kind of do
anything now.

00:18:45.874 --> 00:18:48.502
I have, like, access
to the ancient divine wisdom.

00:18:48.585 --> 00:18:49.878
Oh, here we are.

00:18:49.962 --> 00:18:51.088
Oh, my God.

00:18:51.171 --> 00:18:53.006
Wait, what?
Oh, my God.

00:18:53.090 --> 00:18:56.260
Oh, my God.

00:18:56.343 --> 00:18:58.470
This is so bizarre.

00:18:58.554 --> 00:19:00.055
What?
No.

00:19:00.138 --> 00:19:01.723
God, this looks awful.

00:19:01.807 --> 00:19:05.936
Oh, my God, these yuppies.
Oh, it looks so different.

00:19:06.019 --> 00:19:09.940
What happened to the wall?
Oh, my God.

00:19:10.023 --> 00:19:11.525
Oh, my God!
Ew, the tile.

00:19:11.608 --> 00:19:12.693
What?

00:19:12.776 --> 00:19:14.194
Oh.
It's bad.

00:19:14.278 --> 00:19:16.738
This doesn't even look
like our place at all.

00:19:20.117 --> 00:19:24.454
Drew, we lived here.

00:19:24.538 --> 00:19:26.290
Yeah.
Yeah, we did.

00:19:26.373 --> 00:19:29.668
No, but... but lived.

00:19:29.751 --> 00:19:33.213
Like, we lived lived here.

00:19:33.297 --> 00:19:35.299
Mm-hmm.

00:19:38.468 --> 00:19:41.722
We were in love.

00:19:41.805 --> 00:19:43.348
Yeah.

00:19:50.898 --> 00:19:53.233
You guys, check this out.
What?

00:19:53.317 --> 00:19:54.568
What?
It's a disco ball.

00:19:54.651 --> 00:19:55.819
Oh, God.
What are you doing?

00:19:55.903 --> 00:19:57.112
We should go.

00:19:57.195 --> 00:19:58.614
Oh, my God, you guys.

00:19:58.697 --> 00:20:00.091
It's a little speaker
and it's Bluetooth.

00:20:00.115 --> 00:20:01.450
No, Dory.
Hold on, one second.

00:20:01.533 --> 00:20:02.576
Oh, my God.

00:20:02.659 --> 00:20:04.578
Let's party.

00:20:04.661 --> 00:20:06.538
Oh, my God.

00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:09.875
This was your favorite song.

00:20:09.958 --> 00:20:11.793
Dory, no.
Come on, dance with me.

00:20:44.117 --> 00:20:45.953
Excuse me!

00:20:46.036 --> 00:20:48.080
What the hell are you doing?
Oh, my God.

00:20:48.163 --> 00:20:50.707
I'm so sorry.
You must be so put off.

00:20:50.791 --> 00:20:53.961
But we used to live here.
Like, live live.

00:20:54.044 --> 00:20:55.712
Get the fuck out!
I'm sorry.

00:20:55.796 --> 00:20:57.214
We're gone.

00:20:57.297 --> 00:20:58.775
Sorry, I love your style.
Just kidding.

00:20:58.799 --> 00:21:01.426
Bye.
Oh, whoa.

00:21:03.095 --> 00:21:06.974
You guys, I haven't watched
the sunset in so long.

00:21:07.057 --> 00:21:09.351
It's incredible.

00:21:09.434 --> 00:21:11.311
And we get
to have it every day.

00:21:20.070 --> 00:21:24.074
I wanna thank you guys
for spending the day with me.

00:21:26.034 --> 00:21:28.787
And I want to say I'm sorry.

00:21:29.746 --> 00:21:32.916
I'm sorry for lying to you.

00:21:34.001 --> 00:21:36.461
I'm sorry for hurting you,

00:21:36.545 --> 00:21:39.840
for turning your lives
upside down,

00:21:39.923 --> 00:21:43.301
for not giving you
what you needed.

00:21:43.385 --> 00:21:47.139
I never gave myself compassion
until now.

00:21:48.765 --> 00:21:52.894
And I've given myself
permission to start over.

00:21:56.523 --> 00:21:59.985
I really hope that you guys
can forgive me.

00:22:00.068 --> 00:22:03.947
But if you can't, I understand.

00:22:04.031 --> 00:22:05.031
And at the very least,

00:22:05.073 --> 00:22:08.452
I just hope that

00:22:08.535 --> 00:22:11.663
you can forgive yourselves.

00:22:13.331 --> 00:22:15.917
I've waited so long
to hear that.

00:22:17.336 --> 00:22:18.837
Will you tell me something?

00:22:18.920 --> 00:22:21.548
Of course.

00:22:21.631 --> 00:22:26.094
Did you kill April?

00:22:30.390 --> 00:22:33.685
Yes.

00:22:33.769 --> 00:22:36.271
I pushed her off
the Staten Island ferry.

00:22:40.442 --> 00:22:43.737
I mean, what you put us
through was so fucked up.

00:22:45.363 --> 00:22:47.115
I don't know what I believe

00:22:47.199 --> 00:22:48.867
or what I think
about enlightenment,

00:22:48.950 --> 00:22:52.037
but I know that I've been
burned so many times by you.

00:22:52.120 --> 00:22:54.331
And I'm not going to fall
for whatever it is

00:22:54.414 --> 00:22:56.142
that you're up to this time.
Do you understand me?

00:22:56.166 --> 00:22:59.086
I have no agenda, Drew.
I promise.

00:22:59.169 --> 00:23:01.004
Except just to spread love
wherever I go.

00:23:01.088 --> 00:23:05.092
I-I promise you this time
that it's different.

00:23:06.301 --> 00:23:09.554
Okay, well, that's good.

00:23:09.638 --> 00:23:12.516
I really do hope
it's different this time,

00:23:12.599 --> 00:23:16.103
because if you think about
the last few years,

00:23:16.186 --> 00:23:20.148
our lives have been insane.

00:23:20.232 --> 00:23:24.194
We went to court
for killing someone.

00:23:24.277 --> 00:23:25.821
Can you believe that?

00:23:25.904 --> 00:23:29.449
You guys all convinced me
to bury a body.

00:23:29.533 --> 00:23:32.786
I mean, the craziest part
of all of it is that

00:23:32.869 --> 00:23:37.791
we actually killed someone.

00:23:38.458 --> 00:23:39.793
You know, I mean,

00:23:39.876 --> 00:23:42.796
can you believe
that we did that?

00:23:51.847 --> 00:23:55.392
It's the fact that
I'm not supposed to laugh.

00:23:55.475 --> 00:23:59.688
It is the sheer
inappropriateness of laughter

00:23:59.771 --> 00:24:02.524
that is making me laugh.

00:24:02.607 --> 00:24:05.110
Your mouth was twinkling.

00:24:05.193 --> 00:24:07.237
Whoo!

00:24:07.320 --> 00:24:10.115
Guys, we can't laugh.
Oh, that makes you bad.

00:24:10.198 --> 00:24:11.616
No, it's okay.

00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:13.785
We have to laugh because
it's too painful, you know.

00:24:13.869 --> 00:24:15.555
And... and we can't change
the past so we laugh.

00:24:15.579 --> 00:24:17.038
We have to.

00:24:17.122 --> 00:24:19.332
It does feel good to just,
you know, speak the truth.

00:24:19.416 --> 00:24:22.961
I mean, I don't feel like
I can remember a time

00:24:23.044 --> 00:24:25.255
where that felt okay, you know?

00:24:25.338 --> 00:24:29.759
I promise you that every day
can feel like today.

00:24:31.928 --> 00:24:34.014
There's so much to live for.

00:24:34.097 --> 00:24:37.267
I mean, we're surrounded
by love and beauty

00:24:37.350 --> 00:24:39.686
and I want you all
to feel the way that I do.

00:24:53.158 --> 00:24:54.798
You don't have another
toothbrush, do you?

00:24:54.868 --> 00:24:58.121
Mm-mm.
Is it weird if you use mine?

00:24:58.205 --> 00:24:59.849
I mean, I'm the one who
hasn't brushed my teeth

00:24:59.873 --> 00:25:01.124
in three weeks.
I don't mind.

00:25:01.208 --> 00:25:02.959
I really don't.
Okay, thanks.

00:25:03.043 --> 00:25:06.338
You're welcome.

00:25:06.421 --> 00:25:07.631
Dory.

00:25:07.714 --> 00:25:10.300
Yeah.
I'm so enchanted by you.

00:25:10.383 --> 00:25:12.135
Like, I want to be
just like you.

00:25:12.219 --> 00:25:14.721
Like, I want to spread love
and truth.

00:25:14.804 --> 00:25:18.225
That is so, so sweet.
And you know something?

00:25:18.308 --> 00:25:20.644
The fact that you can identify
that in me,

00:25:20.727 --> 00:25:23.647
that means that
that aspect you admire in me

00:25:23.730 --> 00:25:25.190
is in you.

00:25:25.273 --> 00:25:26.775
Really?
Yeah.

00:25:26.858 --> 00:25:29.486
You're so generous
with your love.

00:25:29.569 --> 00:25:31.863
And, unfortunately,
that's so rare.

00:25:31.947 --> 00:25:33.865
And it means so much to me
that you're willing

00:25:33.949 --> 00:25:35.492
to give me a second chance.

00:25:35.575 --> 00:25:37.327
And that you see the value
in my experience.

00:25:37.410 --> 00:25:38.912
I mean, I just want
to teach you

00:25:38.995 --> 00:25:41.081
everything that I've learned.

00:25:41.164 --> 00:25:42.874
And, well, I just...

00:25:42.958 --> 00:25:44.685
I just hope you know
how special you are to me.

00:25:44.709 --> 00:25:46.419
You're like my sister.

00:25:46.503 --> 00:25:47.754
I love that.

00:25:47.837 --> 00:25:50.423
Like, I-I want to be,
like, your sister.

00:25:50.507 --> 00:25:52.550
Like, I'd seriously do, like,

00:25:52.634 --> 00:25:55.262
anything you ever need, like,
from here on out.

00:25:55.345 --> 00:25:59.057
Like, I just... I just wanna
be right by your side.

00:25:59.140 --> 00:26:00.600
Well, I would love that.

00:26:07.190 --> 00:26:08.751
Dory, there's something
I wanna tell you.

00:26:08.775 --> 00:26:10.670
I feel like I really need
to come clean about it,

00:26:10.694 --> 00:26:13.613
but I also feel really scared
to tell you.

00:26:13.697 --> 00:26:15.907
Portia, you can
tell me anything.

00:26:18.743 --> 00:26:20.578
I've been...

00:26:20.662 --> 00:26:24.165
intimate with Drew
for, like, a little while now.

00:26:26.042 --> 00:26:28.086
Oh.

00:26:30.714 --> 00:26:32.257
I think that's great.

00:26:32.340 --> 00:26:33.550
Really?
Yeah.

00:26:33.633 --> 00:26:35.260
Seriously, you're not mad?
No.

00:26:35.343 --> 00:26:38.305
I don't believe in this culture
of... of scarcity

00:26:38.388 --> 00:26:41.224
and where people need to
possess other people, you know?

00:26:41.308 --> 00:26:42.642
Love should be free.

00:26:42.726 --> 00:26:45.854
How is it?
Is the sex good?

00:26:45.937 --> 00:26:50.150
I mean, it just feels nice

00:26:50.233 --> 00:26:52.819
to be loved or something.

00:26:52.902 --> 00:26:57.699
Well, I am so happy for you.

00:26:57.782 --> 00:26:59.993
Thank you.

00:27:12.839 --> 00:27:16.509
All right, Dory Sief.
I took your advice,

00:27:16.593 --> 00:27:19.220
and I opened my heart
to your words.

00:27:19.304 --> 00:27:21.890
And I think that
you're onto something.

00:27:21.973 --> 00:27:23.850
I'd like to invite you
to my office

00:27:23.933 --> 00:27:27.020
at Tunnel Industries.

00:27:27.103 --> 00:27:30.482
We have healing to do, Dory.

